reviewText: you can find the same resource in the typescript doc, free youtube vids or online articles.
I expected a little bit more advanced topics. This guide is for absolute beginners.

It's a pretty good overview of typescript. I thought the deep dive of JS classes was not needed as it doesn't have much to do with typescript. I would have liked to see more common problems you are bound to come across in real development when working with typescript and how to solve them and understand the hints typescript gives you. My biggest gripe is the audio is not great as there is a constant white noise and at one point the laptop fans are pretty loud, as well as a constant beeping from a dead smoke detector. If the audio was better I'd give it 4/5.

The course is definitely good for beginners. It will eases you into learning the fundamentals. It says intermediate level but if you are already familiar with typescript but want to go little advanced, this is not for you.
It's a wonderful course to jump start with TypeScript provided you have a basic under standing of JavaScript.
Generally ok, but has some minor technical issues (like background noises and some small mistakes in code)
Solid content, but not much for 10 dollars
G​reat for complete beginers. If you have any knowledge of TypeScript this will be of little use to you.
Nice course on TypeScript. Covered all the basics.

These Guided Projects are perfect for a quick start into a new topic. Also useful as a comprehensive refresher of skills not used in a while. This could become the base for a great catalog of skills to rehearse for for job interviews.
The course was all that I was expecting and the lecturer is so good at explaining!
